<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 939.00/520.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Minister to
                                    Haiti</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Dominican Government informs the American Minister at Santo Domingo
                            that Horacio Vásquez and the two Rodriguez left Porto Rico today for
                            Cuba, bound for Haiti, and that Vásquez will import through Cape Haitien
                            1000 rifles and 500,000 rounds. You will bring this informally before
                            the Foreign Office and say that this Government expects that the
                            projected operations of this party on Haitian territory subversive of
                            Dominican peace will be effectively prevented.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>